g.text: Reaction Speed: Quick! Say something professional.
Suggestion: She's a glib girl, but she liked the wording.
Drama: Yes, you. He's talking about you, you boring stiff.
You: Say nothing -- wait for Kim to lead.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yeah..." She draws the word out. "I'm gonna go with *not raped*. I can't say that stuff about him."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Let me make this 100% clear then, officers. I was not sexually assaulted. Would I be this flippant if I had been?"
You: "Lieutenant, I don't know what to say about this."
Empathy: You get the feeling she might be.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I'm sure there's *one* person in the world who does." A crooked smile. "I mean, there are *so many* people. But let me make this clear: The man in that tree did not rape me."
"I'm sure there's *one* person in the world who does." A crooked smile. "I mean there are *so many* people. But let me make this clear: The man who was hanged from that tree did not rape me."
Rhetoric: The wording -- a verbal eye roll. She's almost disgusted with the platitude you served up.
You: "Are you sure you weren't raped?"
You: "I don't get it. What do you mean *partied*?"
Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""We drank, sir..." She takes a sip..."]
You: "Seems like you had *some* idea. That was nifty."
Interfacing: Still, that's pretty clever tampering. Simple and clever, crossing the lines like that.
You: "The call -- reporting the hanging? That was you?"
Inland Empire: You *pissed* it all away... All of it. Elysium.
Suggestion: Could that have been part of the reason they hanged him?
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Like I said, we met over drinks."
You: "That's all. Just wanted to establish that."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "That it doesn't *matter* anymore. And that we are *alone* now. It was difficult to tell, the song itself was very quiet and soft, but you sounded like a wounded boar, sir. It was hard to understand what you were singing on top of it."
You: "It's one of the first things I remember doing in Elysium."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She presses her elbows against her waist and slowly turns her head.
Drama: It's all very organic -- her mannerisms, her movements. If she's acting, she's quite gifted.
Empathy: No, not an idiot. You're just more of a *sensitive* type. Thinks with his *heart*. This woman's *pain* draws you in.
You: "And, in the process, you broke the landline downstairs."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yeah..." She draws out the word. "I'm gonna go with *not raped*. I don't wanna say that shit about him."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She feeds herself another cigarette.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She feeds herself another cigarette.
Savoir Faire: Warming up your hands relieves stress and anxiety, makes you feel and appear calmer, more comfortable. Seems she's doing that here -- consciously or not.
Empathy: Tearing off his armour, demeaning him, throwing rocks at him...
Drama: It's all very organic -- her mannerisms, her movements. If she's acting, she's quite gifted.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "It's a bit early in the morning for *raped*."
Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""Tell them it's not my style. They'..."]

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Tell them it's not my style. They'll have to, you know -- if they want to jazz up the charges -- they'll have to get someone more..." She searches for the word, then shrugs. "Rapeable."
You: "Why was there a bullet in his head?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I'm confused. Sorry."
You: "Got it. 89% is good enough. Moving on."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yes." She makes a twisting motion with her hands. "We made balloon animals, drank lemonade, inflated a bouncy castle."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Hmh..." She flicks a bit of ash away. "Maybe you don't..." The ash lands on her jumpsuit. She brushes it off.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Sure you do, detective..." She cuts you down to size with her light brown eyes.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "In conclusion, officer -- I'm gonna go with a mild to medium *not raped* here."
Perception (Hearing): You hear cracking in her shoulders.
Empathy: She sincerely thinks it's very cool of you.
You: "Suspect partied with victim. Write it down, Kim."
You: "Did you rim the lemonade glasses with sugar? I like to do that."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yeah, I love that too!" Her voice is girlishly high-pitched now. "We frosted the glasses, I unwrapped my bike, there was a petting zoo with little white rabbits..."
Endurance: Whoah. After so much drinking *and* drugs -- how did they manage it?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Reporting crimes is confidential in Revachol, miss."
Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""We drank, sir..." She takes a sip..."]
You: "And his role in this strike was... what?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "You mean *after* they hanged him?"
You: "Could that be why they lynched him? Jealousy?"

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I hope not." A pause. "Actually, I *know* that's not the reason. I'm careful about that kind of thing. Not crossing the wires, you know. But that's probably where they got the rape idea."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She nods. Silvery cigarette fumes disappear into her mouth...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yes! There was a church in there. A really small church. Like the smallest, saddest church in the whole world. It was about that. And also..."
Encyclopedia: Oh, *that*. Yeah, whooh... the less said about OO, the better.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "No, it didn't sound like there was a fight. It sounded like someone was trashing their room." She takes a sip of her coffee and smiles.
Rhetoric: Then, doesn't life get hard *because* we go on?
You: "It mostly just gets hard, doesn't it?"
You: "Maybe we should stop going on then? Doesn't the 'going on' cause the 'getting harder' part?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Don't be, I was going out later anyway. It didn't bother me."
You: "You're making this up. I would never behave like that."
Volition: Really? Quick, tell me what's under her jumpsuit?
You: Can I trust that guy?
Volition: But when it comes to assessments of character and factual accuracy they are not to be trusted. Not with her.
You: Can I trust any of them *ever again?*
You: "Well, thank you for making the call anyway."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Ah yes." She pours herself some more coffee. "The night before I saw you in the hallway -- and reminded you you're a police officer."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm sorry to have to ask this, but have you had a physical relationship with any of the Hardie boys?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Have I slept with any of them? Yes."
Esprit de Corps: Get a grip, he thinks. At least do your *personal* stuff when I'm not here.
You: "You were asked to say you were assaulted? By the Hardie boys?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "With all due respect, sir, I think we partied a little harder than that."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I made it." She nods. "And I would appreciate it if you didn't tell everyone. In Martinaise they call it *snitching*."
Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""We drank, sir..." She takes a sip..."]
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I guess you can say that, yes. A bit. Lovers is such an emotional word. But there was something there. We did enough drugs for there to be."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Mhm." She looks down at the yard.
You: "It must be hard..." (Point to the yard.) "Seeing him there."
"It must have been hard for you..." (Point to the yard.) "Seeing him there."
"It must have been hard for you..." (Point to the yard.) "Seeing him there."
"It must be hard for you..." (Point to the yard.) "Seeing him there all the time."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I don't know, sir. It was stupid. I was drunk too. I was *probably* afraid the Union was listening in -- locals say they have ears in the wires."
You: "Hold on, what do you mean by -- 'rapeable'?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She dips the cigarette in the lighter's flame and inhales, then looks at you -- with her lungs full of smoke.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I can see the similarity, yes." She breathes out, through her nostrils. The air smells of menthol.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A little, yeah."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "How about we, you know, change the subject to something more light-hearted now?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Not my favourite topic..." She flicks the ash away. "But okay."
Rhetoric: It's impossible to say whether she's being sarcastic or really means it.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I think you might have come to the same conclusion last night. At around two o'clock the disco stopped and there was a change of pace."
You: "Before you was only the room -- the sound of the motor vehicle. Steam in the bathroom. And darkness."
Volition: Soft, light brown eyes look back at you, directly into the space behind your eye sockets. You see the smoke rise from between her painted red lips. She's beautiful...
Suggestion: Don't worry. We will protect you from her beauty. We will *consult* you through the reefs and sounds of her persona.
Drama: Me? What did I do? I'm merely a master thespian...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): The silence broken, she exhales a little cloud of smoke and says...
Logic: You were right to suspect there might be foul play involved with the broken phone line!
You: "Better conclude this part of our talk."
You: "Wait... *partied*. Where have I heard that before?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A lot of partying going on."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Oh yes," she says bitterly. "I've had a great view. From the roof, out of the bathroom window. In my dreams..."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I'm confused. Sorry."
Drama: I'm not picking up any theatre-craft here, sir. The pause is sincere.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Is it?" Squinting, she takes a look around. The spring sun is high in the sky; people pass below.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "It *is* afternoon." She looks into her coffee cup. "Time flies, man."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Not explicitly, but I understood what they meant. It wouldn't hurt to spice things up a bit -- some assault and battery, *sexual* assault maybe. It was clear the latter would be *spicier*."
You: "You were asked to say you were assaulted? By the Hardie boys?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "You know how it is."
You: "It sounds like something happened, and you don't want to acknowledge it."
Perception (Hearing): You hear cracking in her shoulders.
You: "What kind of partying?" (Point to your bloated face.) "The kind I do?"
Electrochemistry: You get the feeling she's done enough opiates -- and needed enough NACRA -- to still be flippant if her arm were cut off and fed to her.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Oh, it is." She takes a long drag. "You're still *alive*."
Empathy: With longing. She misses him.
Reaction Speed: Agape? Ready to catch a bullet? A coincidence? Make a note and return to it later.
Kim Kitsuragi: "So am I. Were you aware that he had also been shot, miss?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Which *ones*, sir -- I don't remember precisely. Titus, obviously. But as I said, it's been a long winter."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Over drinks. It's been a long, boring winter."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Men like that? I don't know..." Another pause. "It's the way their imaginations work. I suspect it's what they'd like to do to me."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Oh yes, various artists. Ostentatious Orchestrations prime among them." She arches her eyebrow, waiting for it to connect with you.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yes, you're just one room away." She pours herself more coffee. "Very personal."
Jump to: [Conceptualization: "The date of your re-entry into the..."]
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I was." She takes a sip. "It was the night before I saw you in the hallway -- and reminded you you're a police officer."
Conceptualization: The date of your re-entry into the fossil record.
You: Does this mean she's been lying to me?
Suggestion: She likes you. The Crownhead is a boring condom. He's jealous. This is human nature.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She fishes a cigarette out of her pack and lights it -- then looks at you with her lungs full of smoke.
You: "Forget about it. I don't wanna talk about this shit."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "By 'sexually assaulted' you mean 'raped'?" She takes a quick drag, unperturbed.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "It *is* -- it's murderously early. I'm amazed I'm awake. Why *am* I even awake?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Sure you do, apocalypse cop..." She cuts you down to size with her light brown eyes.
You: "What *did* happen between you and the victim?"
You: "Sexual assault is a serious matter. I need a serious statement from you."
Kim Kitsuragi: "What did you do? When you *partied*?"
You: "What did you do? During these parties."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Downstairs." She taps on the roof with her 10 cm heel. "At the bar. He was on some sort of assignment -- a military man, as you probably know. Had a cool, scary scar."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You called us. The RCM..."
Composure: He takes a small step closer.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Thanks." She manages a smile.
You: "How do the Hardie boys know you?"
"Again -- how do the Hardie boys know you?"
Interfacing: That's some clever tampering. Simple and clever, crossing the lines like that.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "The one downstairs, officer. I used the Whirling landline."
Kim Kitsuragi: "He won't be down there long, miss. We will move the body to the morgue soon."
Electrochemistry: She sees them in each other's arms.
Logic: There *must* be more to it. You should return to this topic after you've talked about her relationship with the deceased, maybe?
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Okay. What should we talk about now?" She takes a drag of her cigarette.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A slow, sad song started playing. Like organ music, on repeat. That went on for quite a while. Some of that time you were yelling along to it."
You: "Are you sure I wasn't being assaulted?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Wow," she nods. "Elysium. You don't hear that term often."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yes." She looks at you. "Never."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Cowering. I was cowering downstairs with Sylvie."
Authority: Me? Get outta here, I'm solid.
Volition: I think it's safe to assume: yes. Mr. Thespian here hasn't been speaking up. If he were, I suspect there would be paeans to her truthfulness. Like this...
Drama: Yes, you. He's talking about you, you boring stiff.
Drama: She isth a laedy most fair and juste!
Volition: Good. The less paranoid option. You can trust them. Just not with *her*.
Good. The less paranoid option. You can trust them. Just not with Klaasje Amandou.
Perception (Sight): A light green speck, and imperfection, on the outer rim of her right iris. It sparkles...
Logic: Good. Yes. This means she could have heard something. Like what you were doing before you blacked out.
Logic: So *she's* Garte's mystery phone cutter!
Jump to: [You: ""Did you... hear something? Sunday..."]
Inland Empire: As she says so you feel the young woman looking at you... and get a *feeling* you can't quite put your finger on. A suspicion?
Rhetoric: 'Spicier'. Of course. Rape's nothing but a plot device for these guys -- to throw around as they wish.
Perception (Sight): There are numerous cigarette burns on those silvery scales -- easy to see now that you're closer.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Sure you do, you disco animal..." She cuts you down to size with her light brown eyes.
You: "No one deserves to be raped."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I would like it to have been that way. But... it wasn't."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "*Untraditionally*, officer." She puts out her Astra, but lights another one with its end first.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A little. The drugs were good enough -- and we did enough of them."
Pain Threshold: A bitter cringe. It *hurts*. You look to the lieutenant...
Kim Kitsuragi: "The voice was disguised," he asks, clearly wishing to distract her from the images. "Did you?..."
You: "I've also seen him in a dream."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I think he was in a security detail. He was ex-military. Worked for Wild Pines; against the Union. We didn't discuss work much, if you know what I mean. But I understood it was dangerous."
You: "And you think they lynched him for it?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "They're frequent guests. Downstairs." She looks at the floor. It's tarred. "They have a booth for Union members. They're probably down there now."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "No. Not as hard."
You: "I had something else. Before we go. A little thing."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "It would appear so. At around two o'clock the disco stopped and there was a change of pace."
You: "Yes. Before I emerged like paleolithic megafauna."
Conceptualization: Nothing. Just time passing. Don't worry.
Volition: These guys are compromised. She's got them singing along to her tune. The little bleeps and bloops you trust for info -- you can't trust them anymore.
Authority: Yes, you. He's talking about you, you grovelling sycophant.
You: (Say it out loud.) "Miss, are you manipulating me?"
Volition: You can't draw a sound conclusion. The one who usually does says...
You: Which ones exactly are affected?
Volition: It's better to know you're being played than to be played without knowing it, is it not?
Endurance: Air moves in your windpipe. Your heart beats. You're a detective -- get back to detecting.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I didn't exactly *disguise* it. I just muffled the mic and nicked the landline a little."
Esprit de Corps: In my dream, he thinks, he said I've failed his children... you glance at the lieutenant. Then back to her.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I think he was in a security detail. He was ex-military. Worked for Wild Pines -- and against the Union. We didn't discuss work much, if you know what I mean. But I understood it was dangerous."
Logic: It's hard to know what to think about that answer.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Apologies, that didn't come out very well. I meant someone who would go along with the lie."
You: "You mean like a birthday party?"
You: "You're being sarcastic. That's not actually how you partied."
You: "*No one* parties harder than me."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "We drank, sir..." She takes a sip of her coffee. "A lot. For weeks basically. We had that effect on each other -- we made each other drink harder. That's why I liked him."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I know it's difficult, miss. We can return to it later."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Then you started screaming and trashed the place."
Volition: She looks back, time moves slowly. The triangles of her face rearranging into a weary smile...
Electrochemistry: Me? What have I done this time?
Volition: I have bad news for you.
Volition: There's nothing you can do about it. You are how you are -- and she is how she is. Things will go as they do.
You: "Please tell me there wasn't anything *else*."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You do *not* need to know that." The lieutenant taps on his notebook. "What you need is to ask normal police questions -- like..." He waits for you to finish the sentence.
Empathy: She's just tired. Don't push her too much.
You: "Where were you when this happened?"
Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""It's a bit early in the morning fo..."]
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Something *difficult*?" She raises her eyebrows. "I've been through at least half a dozen difficult things -- which one do you mean?"
You: "And what does that mean? Were you..."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "It *is* evening." She looks into her coffee cup. "Time flies, man."
You: "What can you tell me about him. Name, eyes, age..."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Hmh..." She flicks a bit of ash away. "Maybe you *don't* know." The ash lands on her jumpsuit. She brushes it off.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Let me make this 100% clear then, officer. I was not sexually assaulted. Would I be this flippant if I had been?"
You: "Harder than this?" (Keep pointing to your face.) "I didn't know it was physically possible."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I made the call. And I would appreciate it if you didn't tell everyone. In Martinaise they call it *snitching*."
You: "Before we go on -- if it's *snitching* then why do it?"
Empathy: She hunches her shoulders a bit, making herself smaller.
You: "Why go through all the trouble?"
You: "That's so *me*. What did I do?"
Perception (Hearing): Her hair brushes her shoulders, making a small hissing sound, almost imperceptible...
Volition: There's no way of knowing. At the moment I'm afraid it's best to assume...
Composure: Me? No way, I'm straight, man.
Composure: Yes, he's talking about you, you shifty asshole.
Volition: Yes. Mr. Thespian here has been singing paeans to how truthful she is...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Oh yes," she says bitterly. "I have *multiple* viewpoints. From the roof, out of the bathroom window. In my dreams..."
Endurance: She must be very cold. And exhausted of this life.
Half Light: You *do* know how it is.
Empathy: She sounds positively *buoyant*. Vivacious. Totally unbothered.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Pretty much." She cradles her coffee cup in both hands.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Are you saying that you were *asked* to tell us you were assaulted?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Let me make this 100% clear then, officer. I was not sexually assaulted." She tilts her head. "Would I be as flippant if I had been?"
Inland Empire: She meant she sees him in her dreams.
Drama: We're not *entirely* convinced about that answer, but okay -- let it slide. Pushing won't help here.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A month ago? Something like that."
You: "What did they hang him for, if not rape?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "And his role in this strike was... what?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "How did you two meet?" The lieutenant's voice is quiet, calm.
Inland Empire: Your imagination starts whirring, whether you want it to or not.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I'm sorry, I can't do it." She puffs on her cigarette. "Not right now. Later maybe. I keep seeing him. Like he is now. I can't talk about his -- I don't know -- *hair...*" Another puff, more nervous.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "You have? Not like I do, I imagine." She's run out of cigarette -- time to light a new one.
Logic: Jigsaw falling into place. This is satisfying. Good catch, I appreciate the symmetry.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yes. And then he's dead. His mouth agape..." She looks into the light green pack of cigarettes and pulls out another one, preparing to light it.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Funny," the lieutenant says softly.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Like you partied with the deceased?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "And they lynched him for it?"
You: "It prides me to hear this. Tell me there was more."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Wow," she nods. "That's some creation myth stuff right there."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I went out afterwards, everything was quiet by then. Around four or five." She nods. "And that was it."
Savoir Faire: Miss Oranje Disco Dancer... You want to put your hand on her back and feel it arch.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A window was smashed. The tape player probably -- the song stopped -- and furniture too. A real *destructothon*. There was screaming. Then, I think, you passed out."
Logic: This is beginning to get *confusing* for you too and we don't like that. Where was she last Sunday night?
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Wow," she nods. "Mythopoetically adequate stuff."
Drama: We will see through deceits. You are shielded. You are wise.
Electrochemistry: You are advised. There are muscles on long white bones that line her limbs, just below the silver jumpsuit...
Reaction Speed: From Titus. About her and Titus' relationship -- that's where you heard it.
Volition: For a second her face disappears from your cornea. Only a silvery negative remains.
Reaction Speed: ...nothing? Someone else was supposed to chime in, weren't they? And then they didn't -- just me swooshing around in here now. Swoosh!
You: What use is this then?
Volition: Don't worry, it's only been four or five seconds. You've got this.
Volition: In his defence -- to reduce him to such inadequacy, she probably had to employ half-truths more often than outright lies.
You: "I noticed your room is close to mine. I have a personal question."
"Let's return to Sunday night -- the sounds from my room"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Apologies, that didn't come out very well. I meant someone who would go along with the lie."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Miss, were you sexually assaulted recently?"
You: "No, I'm literally satisfied with that answer."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Stimulants. Speed also has that effect -- making you drink harder. And then drinking harder makes you do more speed. It's quite the combination. We also had sex."
You: "Hold on. After so much drinking and drugs... *how?*"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "You don't wanna know." She looks into the pack -- it's light green -- then pulls out a ciggy.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "He had something to do with the strike. One has been roiling since I got here. Rotten timing..." She thinks. "But you probably know all about it."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "There was the usual ruckus," she nods. "Loud disco music."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I don't know about that... at around two o'clock the disco stopped and there was a change of pace."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "OO were *huge* where I come from. I was very young then, of course. Like seven. 'Life gets haaard!'" she says, half-singing. "'But we go ooooooon!'"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): The strange moment ends. It was brief, no longer than 2.2 seconds.
Electrochemistry: Yes, he's talking about you, you sinewy idiot.
Volition: I'm sorry I didn't catch it sooner. It takes conscious effort on your part.
You: (Don't say anything.) Just close your eyes and let the moment pass.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): Her face lights up with laughter. "I don't wanna talk about *shit* either! What shall we talk about instead?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm sorry, miss, but we need a definite statement."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm not." He turns to the woman. "What was your relationship with the man they hanged?"
